text.section:
Goods and services of Maryland Correctional Enterprises may be sold on the open market:
if they are produced or provided by an individual on parole or in a work release program;
if the sale is made to a charitable, civic, educational, fraternal, or religious agency, association, or institution for its own use and not for resale within 1 year of the purchase;
to a person for national defense purposes if not prohibited by an act of Congress;
if they are surplus goods remaining after meeting the forecasted requirements of units of State government and political subdivisions and the goods remain unsold 1 year after being produced;
for use by a contractor or subcontractor in performance of a contract with a unit of State government or any other governmental unit in the State;
as allowed under the Private Sector/Prison Industry Enhancement Certification Program of the United States Department of Justice, Bureau of Justice Assistance; or
if they are related to the preparation or distribution of food or services related to agriculture or seafood processing, when the following conditions are met:
the State labor pools are diminished; and
it has been determined that inmate labor is the available source.
